- This is one of the most common bugs in "find min/max" implementations across languages. The root cause is choosing an identity value (`0`) that belongs to the data domain instead of a true mathematical identity (`-Infinity` for max, `Infinity` for min).
- `Math.max(...arr)` handles negatives correctly but stack-overflows on large arrays (~100k+ elements) because it spreads into function arguments. The loop approach is correct for large inputs -- it just needs the right seed value.
